      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">What Is SOWPODS?</h2>
      <p>SOWPODS — now officially called Collins Scrabble Words (CSW) — is the dictionary used for all international Scrabble tournaments outside North America. The name is a portmanteau of SOW (Scrabble Official Words, the former British list) and OSPD (Official Scrabble Players Dictionary, the North American list). By combining both sources, SOWPODS became the most comprehensive English-language Scrabble dictionary available.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Fact</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">SOWPODS includes British spellings (COLOUR, FAVOUR), Commonwealth vocabulary (CHAPPIE, BROLLY), archaic terms, and scientific words accepted by <span class="text-white font-medium">Collins lexicographers</span> — making it the preferred choice for international play and most online platforms.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why Some Words Aren't in TWL</h2>
      <p>TWL (Tournament Word List) is curated by the North American Scrabble Players Association. Its editors apply stricter inclusion criteria — words must appear in specific North American dictionaries and meet cultural sensitivity guidelines. Words deemed offensive were removed in recent editions, and regional British or Commonwealth terms are often excluded entirely.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ SOWPODS Approach</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Inclusive — accepts words from all English-speaking regions, archaic terms, and international borrowings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ TWL Approach</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Conservative — restricts to North American sources, removes offensive terms, smaller total word count.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The result is a smaller, more conservative word list. This isn't a quality judgement — it's simply a different editorial philosophy. TWL prioritises words familiar to North American English speakers, while SOWPODS casts a wider net across all English-speaking regions.</p>

